@startuml Graph Data Structure

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam classBorderColor #333333
skinparam arrowColor #333333

class Graph {
    public final int numVertices
    public boolean directed

    private String[] names
    private List<int[]>[] adj
}

note right of Graph
    Internal Representation:

    names: ["Alice", "Bob", "Carol", ...]
    Index:  0       1      2

    adj (adjacency list):
    - adj[0] = [{target: 1, weight: 1}, {target: 2, weight: 1}, ...]
    - adj[1] = [{target: 2, weight: 1}, ...]
    - adj[2] = [{target: 0, weight: 1}, ...]
    - ...

    Time Complexity:
    - addEdge(u, v, w): O(1)
    - neighbors(u): O(degree(u))
    - findByName(name): O(V)
end note

class Edge {
    int target
    int weight
}

note right of Edge
    Each edge is stored as int[] = {target, weight}

    Example: Edge from vertex 0 to vertex 1 with weight 1
    {1, 1}

    For a 5000-vertex network:
    - ~32,500 edges
    - Space: O(V + E) = O(5000 + 32500) ≈ 37,500 entries
end note

note right of Graph
    Example: Social Network (3 vertices)
    names[0] = "Alice"
    names[1] = "Bob"
    names[2] = "Carol"
    numVertices = 3
    directed = true
    adj[0] = [{1, 1}, {2, 1}]  // Alice follows Bob, Carol
    adj[1] = [{2, 1}]           // Bob follows Carol
    adj[2] = []                 // Carol follows nobody
end note

Graph --> Edge : contains (in adjacency list)

@enduml
